 of this thread, it doesn't actually cut it to idly speculate what you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> would</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do if you cannot justify your hollow boasts and threats with action.<br><br>Ladies and Gentleman, boys and girls, I present to you EQ's own answer to ..<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Fight Club</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br><br>Essentially, 'Fight Club' would provide a frame-work where players who have been mentioned in this file can resolve matters of honour, restore tarnished reputations, or most likely, be allowed bragging rights by making a particular loathed individual their own, personal bitch.<br><br>If players are to duel then there must be an established rule-set that governs all participants involved in a duel, forming the basis for adjudication. If the duels are to possess any validity then the rule-set must be transparent, adhered to by the participants and adjucated by an adjudicator chosen by both the aggrieved parties.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Basic rule-set:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (i)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Participants <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> agree to adhere to the rule-set <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (ii)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Any participant violating the rules shall be duely disqualified, and the contest be considered lost<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (iii)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> An adjudicator must be agreed upon by the participants<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (iv)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> All buffing must be self-buff only, or from any clickable effeccts from equipment (see rule (v) for further clarification<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (v)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> There shall not be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> outside interference either before or during a duel. This includes - but is not limited to - any beneficial or detrimental buffs<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (vi)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Participants must arrive at the specified location half an hour before the duel to allow time for any previous buffing to have worn off (see rule (v))<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (vii)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A level range restriction (to be decided) will be enforced to ensure a fair contest<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (viii)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> All participants <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> provide a list of the equipment that will be used in the duel 24 hours before the duel is to be held. Any equipment which is deemed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be the owners, or has been loaned for the duration of the duel, will result in disqualification, and the contest be considered lost<br><br>These are fast and loose rules, but if enough people are interested then perhaps we can formulate a set of guidelines, establishing a working frame-work for any contest to take place.<br><br>If there is enough interest then we could create some related threads: (i) Challenge declarations (ii) Calendar of forthcoming duels, listing participants and relevant details e.g Name, Class, Level, Equipment and reason for duel, (iii) Results and last (iv) Bragging and bravado.<br><br>Well, what do you think?<br><br>Regards,<br>Riotgirl [Eliza Dushku Form] Hard Woman Enchanter<br><br>&quot;she's like this cleavagey, slut-bomb walking around going 'oh, check me out. i'm wicked cool. i'm five by five'<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=riotgirl>riotgirl</A> at: 2/4/02 4:19:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhubbestubbe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HubbeStubbe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/02 4:20: